```diff
+ import { NextResponse } from &#39;next/server&#39;;
+ import { BenchmarkResult } from &#39;@/lib/types&#39;;
+ 
+ const GITHUB_REPO = &#39;InferenceMAX/InferenceMAX&#39;;
+ 
+ interface GitHubArtifact {
+   id: number;
+   name: string;
+   size_in_bytes: number;
+   archive_download_url: string;
+ }
+ 
+ interface GitHubWorkflowRun {
+   id: number;
+   name: string;
+   created_at: string;
+   conclusion: string;
+   html_url: string;
+ }
+ 
+ export async function GET(request: Request) {
+   const { searchParams } = new URL(request.url);
+   const runId = searchParams.get(&#39;runId&#39;);
+ 
+   try {
+     // Fetch workflow runs
+     const runsResponse = await fetch(
+       &#96;https://api.github.com/repos/${GITHUB_REPO}/actions/runs?per_page=30&#96;,
+       {
+         headers: {
+           &#39;Accept&#39;: &#39;application/vnd.github.v3+json&#39;,
+           ...(process.env.GITHUB_TOKEN &amp;&amp; {
+             &#39;Authorization&#39;: &#96;token ${process.env.GITHUB_TOKEN}&#96;
+           })
+         },
+         next: { revalidate: 300 } // Cache for 5 minutes
+       }
+     );
+ 
+     if (!runsResponse.ok) {
+       throw new Error(&#96;GitHub API error: ${runsResponse.status}&#96;);
+     }
+ 
+     const runsData = await runsResponse.json();
+     const workflowRuns: GitHubWorkflowRun[] = runsData.workflow_runs
+       .filter((run: GitHubWorkflowRun) =&gt; 
+         run.name?.includes(&#39;Sweep&#39;) &amp;&amp; run.conclusion === &#39;success&#39;
+       )
+       .slice(0, 10);
+ 
+     // If a specific run ID is requested, fetch its artifacts
+     if (runId) {
+       const artifactsResponse = await fetch(
+         &#96;https://api.github.com/repos/${GITHUB_REPO}/actions/runs/${runId}/artifacts&#96;,
+         {
+           headers: {
+             &#39;Accept&#39;: &#39;application/vnd.github.v3+json&#39;,
+             ...(process.env.GITHUB_TOKEN &amp;&amp; {
+               &#39;Authorization&#39;: &#96;token ${process.env.GITHUB_TOKEN}&#96;
+             })
+           },
+           next: { revalidate: 300 }
+         }
+       );
+ 
+       if (!artifactsResponse.ok) {
+         throw new Error(&#96;Failed to fetch artifacts: ${artifactsResponse.status}&#96;);
+       }
+ 
+       const artifactsData = await artifactsResponse.json();
+       const resultArtifacts = artifactsData.artifacts.filter(
+         (a: GitHubArtifact) =&gt; a.name.startsWith(&#39;results_&#39;)
+       );
+ 
+       return NextResponse.json({
+         runs: workflowRuns,
+         artifacts: resultArtifacts,
+         selectedRunId: runId
+       });
+     }
+ 
+     return NextResponse.json({
+       runs: workflowRuns,
+       artifacts: [],
+       selectedRunId: null
+     });
+ 
+   } catch (error) {
+     console.error(&#39;Error fetching benchmark data:&#39;, error);
+     return NextResponse.json(
+       { error: &#39;Failed to fetch benchmark data&#39;, details: String(error) },
+       { status: 500 }
+     );
+   }
+ }
+ 
+ // Parse benchmark results from artifact content
+ export function parseBenchmarkResults(content: string, runDate: string, runId: string): BenchmarkResult[] {
+   const lines = content.trim().split(&#39;\n&#39;);
+   const results: BenchmarkResult[] = [];
+ 
+   // Skip header line
+   for (let i = 1; i &lt; lines.length; i++) {
+     const parts = lines[i].split(&#39;\t&#39;);
+     if (parts.length &lt; 17) continue;
+ 
+     try {
+       // Extract model name from path
+       const modelPath = parts[0];
+       const modelName = modelPath.split(&#39;/&#39;).pop()?.replace(/-fp4.*$/, &#39;&#39;) || modelPath;
+ 
+       results.push({
+         model: modelName,
+         hardware: parts[1],
+         framework: parts[2],
+         precision: parts[3],
+         isl: parseInt(parts[4]),
+         osl: parseInt(parts[5]),
+         tp: parseInt(parts[6]),
+         ep: parseInt(parts[7]),
+         dpAttention: parts[8].toLowerCase() === &#39;true&#39;,
+         concurrency: parseInt(parts[9]),
+         ttft: parseFloat(parts[10]),
+         tpot: parseFloat(parts[11]),
+         interactivity: parseFloat(parts[12]),
+         e2el: parseFloat(parts[13]),
+         tputPerGpu: parseFloat(parts[14]),
+         outputTputPerGpu: parseFloat(parts[15]),
+         inputTputPerGpu: parseFloat(parts[16]),
+         runDate,
+         runId
+       });
+     } catch (e) {
+       console.error(&#39;Error parsing line:&#39;, lines[i], e);
+     }
+   }
+ 
+   return results;
+ }
+
```

```diff
+
```

```diff
+     });
+     return values;
+   }, [data]);
+

+       &lt;div className=&quot;p-4 border-b border-cyber-border flex items-center justify-between&quot;&gt;
+         &lt;h3 className=&quot;text-lg font-semibold text-cyber-text&quot;&gt;Benchmark Results&lt;/h3&gt;
+         &lt;div className=&quot;flex items-center gap-4&quot;&gt;
+           &lt;span className=&quot;text-sm text-cyber-muted&quot;&gt;
+             {filteredAndSortedData.length} results
+           &lt;/span&gt;
+           &lt;input
+             type=&quot;text&quot;
+             placeholder=&quot;Search...&quot;
+             value={searchTerm}
+             onChange={(e) =&gt; setSearchTerm(e.target.value)}
+             className=&quot;bg-cyber-bg border border-cyber-border rounded-md px-3 py-1.5 text-sm text-cyber-text
+                        focus:outline-none focus:border-cyber-accent focus:ring-1 focus:ring-cyber-accent/50
+                        placeholder:text-cyber-muted&quot;
+           /&gt;
+         &lt;/div&gt;
+       &lt;/div&gt;
+       
+       &lt;div className=&quot;overflow-x-auto max-h-[600px] overflow-y-auto&quot;&gt;
+         &lt;table className=&quot;data-table w-full text-sm&quot;&gt;
+           &lt;thead&gt;
+             &lt;tr&gt;
+               {COLUMNS.map((col) =&gt; (
+                 &lt;th
+                   key={col.key}
+                   onClick={() =&gt; handleSort(col.key)}
+                   className={&#96;px-3 py-3 text-left text-xs font-semibold text-cyber-muted uppercase tracking-wider 
+                              cursor-pointer hover:text-cyber-accent transition-colors border-b border-cyber-border
+                              ${col.width || &#39;&#39;}&#96;}
+                 &gt;
+                   &lt;div className=&quot;flex items-center gap-1&quot;&gt;
+                     &lt;span&gt;{col.label}&lt;/span&gt;
+                     {col.unit &amp;&amp; (
+                       &lt;span className=&quot;text-[10px] text-cyber-muted/60&quot;&gt;({col.unit})&lt;/span&gt;
+                     )}
+                     {sortField === col.key &amp;&amp; (
+                       &lt;span className=&quot;text-cyber-accent&quot;&gt;
+                         {sortDirection === &#39;asc&#39; ? &#39;↑&#39; : &#39;↓&#39;}
+                       &lt;/span&gt;
+                     )}
+                   &lt;/div&gt;
+                 &lt;/th&gt;
+               ))}
+             &lt;/tr&gt;
+           &lt;/thead&gt;
+           &lt;tbody&gt;
+             {filteredAndSortedData.map((row, idx) =&gt; (
+               &lt;tr 
+                 key={&#96;${row.runId}-${idx}&#96;}
+                 className=&quot;border-b border-cyber-border/50 hover:bg-cyber-accent/5 transition-colors&quot;
+               &gt;
+                 {COLUMNS.map((col) =&gt; {
+                   const value = row[col.key];
+                   const colorClass = typeof value === &#39;number&#39; &amp;&amp; columnValues[col.key]
+                     ? getValueColor(col.key, value, columnValues[col.key])
+                     : &#39;&#39;;
+                   
+                   return (
+                     &lt;td 
+                       key={col.key} 
+                       className={&#96;px-3 py-2 text-cyber-text whitespace-nowrap ${colorClass}&#96;}
+                     &gt;
+                       {col.key === &#39;model&#39; ? (
+                         &lt;span className=&quot;font-medium text-cyber-accent/90&quot;&gt;{formatValue(value, col.key)}&lt;/span&gt;
+                       ) : (
+                         formatValue(value, col.key)
+                       )}
+                     &lt;/td&gt;
+                   );
+                 })}
+               &lt;/tr&gt;
+             ))}
+           &lt;/tbody&gt;
+         &lt;/table&gt;
+       &lt;/div&gt;
+     &lt;/div&gt;
+   );
+ }
+ 
```

</details>

```diff
+               &lt;/div&gt;
+             &lt;/div&gt;
```

```diff
- 
+ # InferenceMAX Dashboard
+ 
+ A modern benchmark dashboard for visualizing LLM inference performance data from [InferenceMAX](https://inferencemax.semianalysis.com/).
+ 
+ ![Dashboard Preview](https://via.placeholder.com/800x400?text=InferenceMAX+Dashboard)
+ 
+ ## Features
+ 
+ - 📊 **Interactive Charts**: Throughput vs Latency scatter plots with customizable axes
+ - 📈 **Trend Analysis**: Historical performance trends over time
+ - 🔍 **Advanced Filtering**: Filter by model, hardware, framework, precision, and sequence lengths
+ - 📋 **Sortable Data Table**: Full benchmark results with search and sort capabilities
+ - 🎨 **Cyberpunk UI**: Modern dark theme with neon accents
+ 
+ ## Metrics Displayed
+ 
+ | Metric | Description |
+ |--------|-------------|
+ | TTFT | Time to First Token (ms) |
+ | TPOT | Time per Output Token (ms) |
+ | E2EL | End-to-End Latency (s) |
+ | TPUT/GPU | Throughput per GPU (tokens/s) |
+ | Interactivity | Tokens per second per user |
+ 
+ ## Getting Started
+ 
+ ### Prerequisites
+ 
+ - Node.js 18+ 
+ - npm or yarn
+ 
+ ### Installation
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;bash
+ # Install dependencies
+ npm install
+ 
+ # Run development server
+ npm run dev
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) to view the dashboard.
+ 
+ ### Environment Variables (Optional)
+ 
+ For higher GitHub API rate limits, set:
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;bash
+ GITHUB_TOKEN=your_github_token
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ## Data Source
+ 
+ Benchmark data is sourced from [InferenceMAX GitHub Actions](https://github.com/InferenceMAX/InferenceMAX/actions).
+ 
+ The project runs nightly benchmarks on:
+ - **Hardware**: GB200, B200, H100, A100
+ - **Frameworks**: DYNAMO-TRTLLM, DYNAMO-SGLANG, SGLANG, VLLM
+ - **Models**: DeepSeek-R1, GPT-OSS, and more
+ - **Precisions**: FP4, FP8, FP16
+ 
+ ## Tech Stack
+ 
+ - **Framework**: Next.js 14
+ - **Styling**: Tailwind CSS
+ - **Charts**: Recharts
+ - **Language**: TypeScript
+ 
+ ## Related Links
+ 
+ - [InferenceMAX Official Site](https://inferencemax.semianalysis.com/)
+ - [InferenceMAX GitHub](https://github.com/InferenceMAX/InferenceMAX)
+ - [SemiAnalysis](https://semianalysis.com/)
+ 
+ ## License
+ 
+ MIT
+
```

`.env.local` 文件被保护了，我来告诉你如何手动设置：

## 设置 GitHub Token 的步骤:

```bash
# 在终端运行:
echo "GITHUB_TOKEN=your_token_here" > /root/aa/.env.local
```

**获取 Token 的步骤:**
1. 访问 https://github.com/settings/tokens
2. 点击 "Generate new token (classic)"
3. 勾选 `repo` 和 `actions:read` 权限
4. 复制 token 替换 `your_token_here`

```diff
+ import { BenchmarkResult, WorkflowRun } from &#39;./types&#39;;
+ 
+ const GITHUB_REPO = &#39;InferenceMAX/InferenceMAX&#39;;
+ const WORKFLOW_FILE = &#39;full-sweep-1k1k-scheduler.yml&#39;;
+ 
+ export async function fetchWorkflowRuns(token?: string): Promise&lt;WorkflowRun[]&gt; {
+   const allRuns: WorkflowRun[] = [];
+   let page = 1;
+   const perPage = 100;
+ 
+   try {
+     while (true) {
+       const url = &#96;https://api.github.com/repos/${GITHUB_REPO}/actions/workflows/${WORKFLOW_FILE}/runs?status=success&amp;per_page=${perPage}&amp;page=${page}&#96;;
+       
+       const response = await fetch(url, {
+         headers: {
+           &#39;Accept&#39;: &#39;application/vnd.github.v3+json&#39;,
+           ...(token &amp;&amp; { &#39;Authorization&#39;: &#96;token ${token}&#96; })
+         },
+         next: { revalidate: 300 }
+       });
+ 
+       if (!response.ok) {
+         console.error(&#96;GitHub API error: ${response.status}&#96;);
+         break;
+       }
+ 
+       const data = await response.json();
+       const runs = data.workflow_runs || [];
+       
+       if (runs.length === 0) break;
+ 
+       allRuns.push(...runs.map((run: any) =&gt; ({
+         id: run.id,
+         name: run.name,
+         created_at: run.created_at,
+         conclusion: run.conclusion,
+         html_url: run.html_url,
+         head_sha: run.head_sha,
+         run_number: run.run_number
+       })));
+ 
+       if (runs.length &lt; perPage) break;
+       page++;
+       
+       // Limit to avoid rate limiting
+       if (page &gt; 5) break;
+     }
+   } catch (error) {
+     console.error(&#39;Error fetching workflow runs:&#39;, error);
+   }
+ 
+   return allRuns;
+ }
+ 
+ export async function fetchRunArtifacts(runId: number, token?: string): Promise&lt;any[]&gt; {
+   try {
+     const response = await fetch(
+       &#96;https://api.github.com/repos/${GITHUB_REPO}/actions/runs/${runId}/artifacts&#96;,
+       {
+         headers: {
+           &#39;Accept&#39;: &#39;application/vnd.github.v3+json&#39;,
+           ...(token &amp;&amp; { &#39;Authorization&#39;: &#96;token ${token}&#96; })
+         },
+         next: { revalidate: 300 }
+       }
+     );
+ 
+     if (!response.ok) {
+       console.error(&#96;Failed to fetch artifacts: ${response.status}&#96;);
+       return [];
+     }
+ 
+     const data = await response.json();
+     return data.artifacts || [];
+   } catch (error) {
+     console.error(&#39;Error fetching artifacts:&#39;, error);
+     return [];
+   }
+ }
+ 
+ // Parse TSV/CSV benchmark results
+ export function parseBenchmarkResults(
+   content: string, 
+   runDate: string, 
+   runId: string,
+   commitSha: string
+ ): BenchmarkResult[] {
+   const lines = content.trim().split(&#39;\n&#39;);
+   const results: BenchmarkResult[] = [];
+ 
+   // Skip header line
+   for (let i = 1; i &lt; lines.length; i++) {
+     const line = lines[i].trim();
+     if (!line) continue;
+     
+     const parts = line.split(&#39;\t&#39;);
+     if (parts.length &lt; 17) continue;
+ 
+     try {
+       // Extract model name from path
+       const modelPath = parts[0];
+       const modelName = extractModelName(modelPath);
+ 
+       results.push({
+         model: modelName,
+         hardware: parts[1],
+         framework: parts[2],
+         precision: parts[3],
+         isl: parseInt(parts[4]),
+         osl: parseInt(parts[5]),
+         tp: parseInt(parts[6]),
+         ep: parseInt(parts[7]),
+         dpAttention: parts[8].toLowerCase() === &#39;true&#39;,
+         concurrency: parseInt(parts[9]),
+         ttft: parseFloat(parts[10]),
+         tpot: parseFloat(parts[11]),
+         interactivity: parseFloat(parts[12]),
+         e2el: parseFloat(parts[13]),
+         tputPerGpu: parseFloat(parts[14]),
+         outputTputPerGpu: parseFloat(parts[15]),
+         inputTputPerGpu: parseFloat(parts[16]),
+         runDate,
+         runId,
+         commitSha
+       });
+     } catch (e) {
+       console.error(&#39;Error parsing line:&#39;, line, e);
+     }
+   }
+ 
+   return results;
+ }
+ 
+ function extractModelName(path: string): string {
+   // Extract model name from paths like /mnt/lustre01/models/deepseek-r1-0528-fp4-v2
+   const parts = path.split(&#39;/&#39;);
+   const name = parts[parts.length - 1] || path;
+   // Clean up the name
+   return name.replace(/-fp4.*$/, &#39;&#39;).replace(/-fp8.*$/, &#39;&#39;);
+ }
+ 
+ // Generate a unique config key for grouping
+ export function getConfigKey(result: BenchmarkResult): string {
+   return &#96;${result.model}|${result.hardware}|${result.framework}|${result.precision}|tp${result.tp}|ep${result.ep}|conc${result.concurrency}&#96;;
+ }
+ 
+ export function getConfigLabel(result: BenchmarkResult): string {
+   return &#96;${result.model} / ${result.framework} / tp${result.tp} / conc${result.concurrency}&#96;;
+ }
+
```

```diff
+ function generateHistoricalData(): BenchmarkResult[] {
+   const results: BenchmarkResult[] = [];

+   // Define configurations we want to track over time

+ export function getUniqueValues&lt;T extends keyof BenchmarkResult&gt;(
+   data: BenchmarkResult[], 
+   field: T
+ ): string[] {
+   const values = new Set(data.map(d =&gt; String(d[field])));

+ // Group data by configuration for time series charts
+ export function groupByConfig(data: BenchmarkResult[]): Map&lt;string, BenchmarkResult[]&gt; {
+   const groups = new Map&lt;string, BenchmarkResult[]&gt;();
+   
+   data.forEach(item =&gt; {
+     const key = &#96;${item.model}|${item.hardware}|${item.framework}|${item.precision}|tp${item.tp}|conc${item.concurrency}&#96;;
+     if (!groups.has(key)) {
+       groups.set(key, []);
+     }
+     groups.get(key)!.push(item);
+   });
+ 
+   // Sort each group by date
+   groups.forEach((items, key) =&gt; {
+     groups.set(key, items.sort((a, b) =&gt; a.runDate.localeCompare(b.runDate)));
+   });
+ 
+   return groups;
+ }
+ 
+ // Get config label for display
+ export function getConfigLabel(item: BenchmarkResult): string {
+   const concLabel = item.concurrency &gt;= 9999 ? &#39;qps_inf&#39; : &#96;qps_${item.concurrency}&#96;;
+   return &#96;${item.model} / tp${item.tp} / ${concLabel}&#96;;
+ }
+ 
+ export function getShortConfigLabel(item: BenchmarkResult): string {
+   const concLabel = item.concurrency &gt;= 9999 ? &#39;qps_inf&#39; : &#96;qps_${item.concurrency}&#96;;
+   return &#96;tp${item.tp} / ${concLabel}&#96;;
+ }
```

Dashboard 已更新，现在更像 PyTorch HUD 的风格了！🎉

## 更新内容

### 1. 时间序列图表 (2x2 布局)
- **Latency (s)** - 端到端延迟趋势
- **Median ITL (ms)** - 交互延迟趋势  
- **Median TPOT (ms)** - 每 token 输出时间趋势
- **Median TTFT (ms)** - 首 token 时间趋势

每个图表显示**同一配置在不同时间点**的性能变化，不同颜色代表不同的配置（tp值/concurrency组合）。

### 2. 新增筛选器
- **Time Range**: 7天/14天/30天/全部
- **Granularity**: 按天 或 按 Commit
- **Model/Hardware/Framework/Precision/TP/Concurrency** 过滤

### 3. 数据来源

要从真实的 GitHub Actions 获取数据，请设置 Token：

```bash
# 1. 创建 .env.local 文件
echo "GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx" > /root/aa/.env.local

# 2. 重启服务器
# (Ctrl+C 停止当前服务，然后重新运行)
cd /root/aa && npm run dev
```

**获取 Token:**
1. 打开 https://github.com/settings/tokens
2. 点击 "Generate new token (classic)"
3. 勾选 `repo` 和 `actions:read`
4. 复制 token

### 4. API 端点

```
GET /api/benchmarks?days=30  # 获取最近30天的 workflow runs
POST /api/benchmarks         # 获取特定 run 的 artifacts
```

目前使用的是模拟的历史数据来展示效果。要接入真实数据，需要：
1. 设置 `GITHUB_TOKEN`
2. 从 artifacts 下载并解析结果文件（zip 格式）

你可以在 http://localhost:3000 查看更新后的 Dashboard！

```diff
+ // Download and extract artifact zip
+ export async function downloadArtifact(artifactUrl: string, token: string): Promise&lt;string | null&gt; {
+   try {
+     const response = await fetch(artifactUrl, {
+       headers: {
+         &#39;Accept&#39;: &#39;application/vnd.github.v3+json&#39;,

+       f.endsWith(&#39;.csv&#39;) || 
+       f.endsWith(&#39;.txt&#39;) ||

+     if (resultFile) {

+       return content;
+     }
+ 
+     // If no specific file found, try to get the first text file

+       }
+     }
+ 
+     return null;
+   } catch (error) {
+     console.error(&#39;Error downloading artifact:&#39;, error);
+     return null;
+   }
+ }

+ // Parse benchmark results from TSV content
+ export function parseBenchmarkResults(
+   content: string,
+   runDate: string,
+   runId: string,
+   commitSha: string
+ ): BenchmarkResult[] {
+   const lines = content.trim().split(&#39;\n&#39;);
+   const results: BenchmarkResult[] = [];
+ 
+   if (lines.length &lt; 2) return results;
+ 
+   // Parse header

+   const columnMap = createColumnMap(header);
+ 
+   // Parse data rows

+     const result = parseRow(parts, columnMap, runDate, runId, commitSha);
+     if (result) {
+       results.push(result);
+     }
+   }

+ function parseRow(
+   parts: string[],
+   columnMap: Record&lt;string, number&gt;,
+   runDate: string,
+   runId: string,
+   commitSha: string
+ ): BenchmarkResult | null {

+     const idx = columnMap[key];

+   };

+   const getNum = (key: string, def: number = 0): number =&gt; {
+     const val = getValue(key);
+     if (!val || val === &#39;N/A&#39; || val === &#39;-&#39; || val === &#39;nan&#39;) return def;
+     const num = parseFloat(val);
+     return isNaN(num) ? def : num;

+   const model = extractModelName(modelPath);
+   if (!model) return null;

+   return {

+     hardware: getValue(&#39;hardware&#39;, &#39;Unknown&#39;),
+     framework: getValue(&#39;framework&#39;, &#39;Unknown&#39;),
+     precision: getValue(&#39;precision&#39;, &#39;FP16&#39;),

+     runDate,
+     runId,
+     commitSha
+   };
+ }

+ function extractModelName(path: string): string {
+   if (!path) return &#39;&#39;;
+   const parts = path.split(&#39;/&#39;);
+   let name = parts[parts.length - 1] || path;
+   return name.replace(/-fp[48].*$/i, &#39;&#39;).replace(/-v\d+$/i, &#39;&#39;) || &#39;Unknown&#39;;
+ }

+ // Main function to fetch all benchmark data
+ export async function fetchAllBenchmarkData(
+   token: string,
+   days: number = 30,
+   workflow: string = &#39;full-sweep-1k1k-scheduler.yml&#39;
+ ): Promise&lt;BenchmarkResult[]&gt; {
+   const allResults: BenchmarkResult[] = [];
+   
+   // Get workflow runs
+   const runs = await fetchWorkflowRuns(workflow, token, 5);
+   
+   // Filter by date
+   const cutoff = new Date();
+   cutoff.setDate(cutoff.getDate() - days);
+   
+   const recentRuns = runs.filter(r =&gt; new Date(r.created_at) &gt;= cutoff);
+   
+   // Fetch artifacts for each run
+   for (const run of recentRuns) {
+     const artifacts = await fetchRunArtifacts(run.id, token);
+     const resultArtifacts = artifacts.filter(a =&gt; 
+       a.name.includes(&#39;result&#39;) || a.name.includes(&#39;benchmark&#39;)
+     );
+ 
+     for (const artifact of resultArtifacts) {
+       const content = await downloadArtifact(artifact.archive_download_url, token);
+       if (content) {
+         const runDate = run.created_at.split(&#39;T&#39;)[0];
+         const results = parseBenchmarkResults(content, runDate, String(run.id), run.head_sha);
+         allResults.push(...results);
+       }
+     }
+   }
+ 
+   return allResults;
```

```bash
curl -sL -H "Authorization: token $TOKEN" \
  "https://api.github.com/repos/InferenceMAX/InferenceMAX/actions/artifacts/4690407811/zip" \
  -o /tmp/test_artifact.zip && \
unzip -p /tmp/test_artifact.zip
```

```diff
+ // Process a single run - tries aggregated results first, then individual artifacts
+ async function processRun(
+   run: WorkflowRun,
+   token: string
+ ): Promise&lt;BenchmarkResult[]&gt; {
+   const runDate = run.created_at.split(&#39;T&#39;)[0];
+   const runId = String(run.id);
+   const commitSha = run.head_sha;
+   
+   console.log(&#96;Processing run ${run.id} (${runDate})&#96;);
+   
+   // Fetch all artifacts for this run
+   const artifacts = await fetchAllRunArtifacts(run.id, token);
+   console.log(&#96;  Found ${artifacts.length} total artifacts&#96;);
+   
+   if (artifacts.length === 0) return [];
+   
+   // Strategy 1: Look for aggregated results_* artifacts first
+   const aggregatedArtifacts = artifacts.filter(a =&gt; a.name.startsWith(&#39;results_&#39;));
+   
+   if (aggregatedArtifacts.length &gt; 0) {
+     console.log(&#96;  Using ${aggregatedArtifacts.length} aggregated result artifacts&#96;);
+     const results: BenchmarkResult[] = [];
+     
+     for (const artifact of aggregatedArtifacts) {
+       const content = await downloadArtifact(artifact.id, token);
+       if (content) {
+         const parsed = parseBenchmarkResults(content, runDate, runId, commitSha);
+         results.push(...parsed);
+       }
+     }
+     
+     console.log(&#96;  Got ${results.length} results from aggregated artifacts&#96;);
+     return results;
+   }
+   
+   // Strategy 2: Parse individual artifacts (they contain single JSON results)
+   // Filter for artifacts that look like benchmark results (contain model/config info)
+   const benchmarkArtifacts = artifacts.filter(a =&gt; {
+     const name = a.name.toLowerCase();
+     // Match patterns like: dsr1_1k1k_fp8_sglang_tp8_... or gptoss_1k1k_fp4_vllm_...
+     return (name.includes(&#39;dsr1_&#39;) || name.includes(&#39;gptoss_&#39;) || name.includes(&#39;llama_&#39;) || name.includes(&#39;qwen_&#39;)) &amp;&amp;
+            (name.includes(&#39;_sglang_&#39;) || name.includes(&#39;_vllm_&#39;) || name.includes(&#39;_trt_&#39;) || name.includes(&#39;_dynamo&#39;));
+   });
+   
+   console.log(&#96;  Parsing ${benchmarkArtifacts.length} individual benchmark artifacts&#96;);
+   
+   const results: BenchmarkResult[] = [];
+   
+   // Process in batches to avoid overwhelming the API
+   const batchSize = 20;
+   for (let i = 0; i &lt; benchmarkArtifacts.length; i += batchSize) {
+     const batch = benchmarkArtifacts.slice(i, i + batchSize);
+     
+     const batchResults = await Promise.all(
+       batch.map(async (artifact) =&gt; {
+         const content = await downloadArtifact(artifact.id, token);
+         if (content) {
+           return parseBenchmarkResults(content, runDate, runId, commitSha);
+         }
+         return [];
+       })
+     );
+     
+     results.push(...batchResults.flat());
+     
+     // Small delay between batches
+     if (i + batchSize &lt; benchmarkArtifacts.length) {
+       await new Promise(r =&gt; setTimeout(r, 100));
+     }
+   }

+   return results;
+ }
```

## ✅ 问题已修复！

### 数据统计对比

| 指标 | 修复前 | 修复后 |
|------|--------|--------|
| **总数据点** | 47 | **5,743** 🎉 |
| **硬件平台** | 6 | **10** |
| **框架** | 5 | **6** |
| **日期覆盖** | 2 天 | **13 天** |

### 现在包含的数据

- **📊 模型**: DeepSeek-R1, DeepSeek-R1-0528, GPT-OSS
- **🖥️ 硬件**: B200, B200-NVS, B200-TRT, GB200, H100, H200, H200-TRT, MI300X, MI325X, MI355X
- **⚙️ 框架**: DYNAMO-SGLANG, DYNAMO-TRT, DYNAMO-TRTLLM, SGLANG, TRT, VLLM
- **🎯 精度**: FP4, FP8
- **📅 日期范围**: 2025-11-05 至 2025-11-28

### 修复内容

问题是：GitHub API 分页获取 artifacts 时，一些 runs 有 200+ 个 artifacts，但我们之前只获取了第一页（100 个），导致漏掉了汇总的 `results_*` artifacts。

现在代码会：
1. **完整分页获取**所有 artifacts
2. 优先使用汇总的 `results_*` artifacts（包含完整数据）
3. 如果没有汇总文件，则解析独立的 benchmark artifacts

打开 http://localhost:3000 查看完整的历史趋势数据！📈

```diff
+ interface MultiSelectProps {

+   options: string[];
+   onChange: (values: string[]) =&gt; void;
+   allLabel?: string;

+ export default function MultiSelect({ 
+   label, 
+   values, 
+   options, 
+   onChange,
+   allLabel = &#39;All&#39;
+ }: MultiSelectProps) {
+   const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);
+   const containerRef = useRef&lt;HTMLDivElement&gt;(null);
+ 
+   // Close dropdown when clicking outside
+   useEffect(() =&gt; {
+     function handleClickOutside(event: MouseEvent) {
+       if (containerRef.current &amp;&amp; !containerRef.current.contains(event.target as Node)) {
+         setIsOpen(false);
+       }
+     }
+ 
+     document.addEventListener(&#39;mousedown&#39;, handleClickOutside);
+     return () =&gt; document.removeEventListener(&#39;mousedown&#39;, handleClickOutside);
+   }, []);

+     if (values.includes(option)) {
+       onChange(values.filter(v =&gt; v !== option));
+     } else {

+     }

+   };

+         &lt;span className={values.length &gt; 0 ? &#39;text-blue-400&#39; : &#39;&#39;}&gt;
```

```diff
    { label: &#39;8k/1k&#39;, value: &#39;full-sweep-8k1k-scheduler.yml&#39; },
  ];
+ 
+ // Cache duration: 1 hour
+ const CACHE_DURATION_MS = 60 * 60 * 1000;
+ 
+ interface CacheEntry {
+   data: BenchmarkResult[];
+   runsCount: number;
+   timestamp: number;
+ }
+ 
+ function getCacheKey(workflow: string, days: number): string {
+   return &#96;benchmark_cache_${workflow}_${days}&#96;;
+ }
+ 
+ function getFromCache(workflow: string, days: number): CacheEntry | null {
+   if (typeof window === &#39;undefined&#39;) return null;
+   
+   try {
+     const key = getCacheKey(workflow, days);
+     const cached = localStorage.getItem(key);
+     if (!cached) return null;
+     
+     const entry: CacheEntry = JSON.parse(cached);
+     const now = Date.now();
+     
+     // Check if cache is still valid
+     if (now - entry.timestamp &lt; CACHE_DURATION_MS) {
+       return entry;
+     }
+     
+     // Cache expired, remove it
+     localStorage.removeItem(key);
+     return null;
+   } catch {
+     return null;
+   }
+ }
+ 
+ function saveToCache(workflow: string, days: number, data: BenchmarkResult[], runsCount: number): void {
+   if (typeof window === &#39;undefined&#39;) return;
+   
+   try {
+     const key = getCacheKey(workflow, days);
+     const entry: CacheEntry = {
+       data,
+       runsCount,
+       timestamp: Date.now()
+     };
+     localStorage.setItem(key, JSON.stringify(entry));
+   } catch {
+     // Storage might be full, ignore
+   }
+ }
```

已修复缓存问题！主要改动：

## 修复内容

1. **缓存检查改为同步执行**
   - 之前：`useEffect` 内异步检查缓存，导致首次渲染总是显示 "Loading..."
   - 现在：在 `useEffect` 开头同步检查缓存，有缓存时直接设置数据，**不触发加载动画**

2. **Loading 状态改为三态**
   - `null` = 尚未检查
   - `true` = 正在加载
   - `false` = 加载完成

3. **添加日志帮助调试**
   - 控制台会打印 "Using cached data: X items" 或 "Fetched and cached data: X items"

## 现在的行为

| 场景 | 表现 |
|------|------|
| **首次加载** | 显示 "Fetching benchmark data from GitHub..." |
| **刷新页面（有缓存）** | 直接显示数据，显示 "✓ Cached" |
| **点击 Refresh** | 强制重新获取，更新缓存 |
| **缓存过期（1小时后）** | 自动重新获取 |

已修复！主要改动：

## 问题原因

数据量太大（15551 条记录），**localStorage 只有 5-10MB 限制**，无法存储这么多数据。

## 解决方案

改用 **IndexedDB** 存储缓存数据：
- IndexedDB 容量通常 **50MB+**
- 支持存储大量结构化数据
- 浏览器原生支持

## 其他改进

1. **防止重复请求** - 使用 `useRef` 追踪请求状态，避免同时发起多个请求
2. **更好的日志** - 控制台会显示：
   - `Cache hit! 15551 items` - 命中缓存
   - `Cache saved! 15551 items` - 缓存成功保存
   - `No cache found, fetching from API...` - 需要获取数据

## 测试方法

1. 刷新页面，等待数据加载完成（看到控制台 `Cache saved!`）
2. 再次刷新页面
3. 应该看到 `Cache hit!` 并且直接显示数据，不再请求 API

打开浏览器控制台 (F12) 可以看到缓存状态日志。现在刷新页面试试！🚀

```diff
+ const CACHE_DIR = path.join(process.cwd(), &#39;.cache&#39;);
+ 
+ interface CacheEntry {
+   data: BenchmarkResult[];
+   runs: WorkflowRun[];
+   timestamp: number;
+   workflow: string;
+   days: number;

+ // In-memory cache
+ const memoryCache = new Map&lt;string, CacheEntry&gt;();
+ 
+ function getCacheKey(workflow: string, days: number): string {
+   return &#96;${workflow}_${days}&#96;;
+ }
+ 
+ function getCacheFilePath(workflow: string, days: number): string {
+   const safeWorkflow = workflow.replace(/[^a-zA-Z0-9]/g, &#39;_&#39;);
+   return path.join(CACHE_DIR, &#96;cache_${safeWorkflow}_${days}.json&#96;);
+ }
+ 
+ function ensureCacheDir(): void {
+   if (!fs.existsSync(CACHE_DIR)) {
+     fs.mkdirSync(CACHE_DIR, { recursive: true });
+   }
+ }
+ 
+ function getFromCache(workflow: string, days: number): CacheEntry | null {
+   const key = getCacheKey(workflow, days);
+   const now = Date.now();
+ 
+   // Check memory cache first
+   const memCached = memoryCache.get(key);
+   if (memCached &amp;&amp; (now - memCached.timestamp) &lt; CACHE_DURATION_MS) {
+     console.log(&#96;[Cache] Memory cache hit for ${key}&#96;);
+     return memCached;
+   }
+ 
+   // Check file cache
+   try {
+     const filePath = getCacheFilePath(workflow, days);
+     if (fs.existsSync(filePath)) {
+       const fileContent = fs.readFileSync(filePath, &#39;utf-8&#39;);
+       const cached: CacheEntry = JSON.parse(fileContent);
+       
+       if ((now - cached.timestamp) &lt; CACHE_DURATION_MS) {
+         console.log(&#96;[Cache] File cache hit for ${key}&#96;);
+         // Restore to memory cache
+         memoryCache.set(key, cached);
+         return cached;
+       } else {
+         console.log(&#96;[Cache] File cache expired for ${key}&#96;);
+         // Delete expired cache file
+         fs.unlinkSync(filePath);
+       }
+     }
+   } catch (err) {
+     console.error(&#39;[Cache] Error reading file cache:&#39;, err);
+   }
+ 
+   return null;
+ }
+ 
+ function saveToCache(workflow: string, days: number, data: BenchmarkResult[], runs: WorkflowRun[]): void {
+   const key = getCacheKey(workflow, days);
+   const entry: CacheEntry = {
+     data,
+     runs,
+     timestamp: Date.now(),
+     workflow,
+     days
+   };
+ 
+   // Save to memory cache
+   memoryCache.set(key, entry);
+   console.log(&#96;[Cache] Saved to memory cache: ${key} (${data.length} items)&#96;);
+ 
+   // Save to file cache for persistence
+   try {
+     ensureCacheDir();
+     const filePath = getCacheFilePath(workflow, days);
+     fs.writeFileSync(filePath, JSON.stringify(entry));
+     console.log(&#96;[Cache] Saved to file cache: ${filePath}&#96;);
+   } catch (err) {
+     console.error(&#39;[Cache] Error writing file cache:&#39;, err);
+   }
+ }
  
  export async function GET(request: Request) {
```

完成！现在使用**服务端缓存**：

## 缓存机制

| 类型 | 说明 |
|------|------|
| **内存缓存** | 快速访问，服务重启后失效 |
| **文件缓存** | 持久化到 `.cache/` 目录，服务重启后仍有效 |
| **缓存时长** | 1 小时 |

## 工作流程

```
用户请求 → 检查内存缓存 → 检查文件缓存 → 从GitHub获取 → 保存缓存
           ↓                ↓                ↓
         命中返回          命中返回          返回并缓存
```

## 日志示例

```
[Cache] Memory cache hit for full-sweep-1k1k-scheduler.yml_365
[Cache] File cache hit for full-sweep-1k1k-scheduler.yml_365  
[API] Fetching fresh data from GitHub for ... (首次获取)
[Cache] Saved to memory cache: ... (15551 items)
[Cache] Saved to file cache: .cache/cache_...json
```

## 前端显示

- **"✓ Cached (5m ago)"** - 使用服务端缓存，显示缓存时间
- **Refresh 按钮** - 强制刷新，绕过缓存重新获取

## 多用户优势

1. 第一个用户访问 → 从 GitHub 获取数据 → 保存到服务器缓存
2. 后续用户访问 → 直接使用服务器缓存 → **毫秒级响应**
3. 1 小时后缓存过期 → 下次请求重新获取

现在刷新页面试试！第一次会慢（从 GitHub 获取），之后会快很多！🚀

---

完成！现在使用 `fetchKeyRef` 来防止重复请求：

## 修复逻辑

```typescript
const fetchKeyRef = useRef<string | null>(null);

useEffect(() => {
  const key = `${workflow}_${dateRange}`;
  
  // 如果已经在获取同样的数据，跳过
  if (fetchKeyRef.current === key) {
    return;
  }
  fetchKeyRef.current = key;
  
  // ... fetch data
}, [dateRange, workflow]);
```

## 工作原理

| 场景 | 结果 |
|------|------|
| 首次加载 | 发起请求，设置 key |
| StrictMode 第二次调用 | 检测到相同 key，**跳过请求** |
| 切换 workflow/dateRange | 新 key，发起新请求 |
| 点击 Refresh | 使用带时间戳的唯一 key |

刷新页面试试，现在只会看到一次 API 请求了！🎉

完成！已将 "Median TPOT (ms)" 改为 "Output Speed (tok/s)"：

## 转换公式

```
token/s = 1000 / TPOT(ms)
```

例如：
- TPOT = 50ms → 1000/50 = **20 tok/s**
- TPOT = 25ms → 1000/25 = **40 tok/s**

## 代码改动

```tsx
<TimeSeriesChart
  data={filteredData}
  metric="tpot"
  title="Output Speed (tok/s)"
  unit="tok/s"
  transform={(ms) => 1000 / ms}  // 新增转换函数
/>
```

刷新页面即可看到效果！现在图表会显示每秒生成的 token 数量，数值越高越好。🚀

完成！交互逻辑已更新：

## 新的交互方式

| 操作 | 效果 |
|------|------|
| **单击** | 只显示这一条线（隐藏其他所有） |
| **⌘/Ctrl + 点击** | 切换这条线（添加到/移除出当前显示） |
| **Show All** | 显示全部 |

## 使用场景

1. **想看单个模型**：直接点击图例
2. **想对比两个模型**：点击第一个 → ⌘+点击第二个
3. **想对比多个模型**：继续 ⌘+点击添加更多
4. **想移除某个模型**：⌘+点击已显示的模型
5. **恢复全部**：点击 "Show All"

图例项悬停时会显示提示 `"Click: show only this | Cmd/Ctrl+Click: toggle"`

刷新页面试试！🎯
